description:
&lt;h1&gt;Bank Health Visitor, Band 6&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Universal Children’s Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a registered nurse / midwife with a Specialist Community Public Health Nursing qualification? Are you looking for flexible NHS bank opportunities to fit around your lifestyle? If so, this could be the place for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a team who are supportive, dedicated and always go the extra mile for the children and families. To assist you in your role, you will receive professional supervision and support including Child Protection Supervision. We are committed to providing all our clinicians with regular learning and development which will enable you to practice at a high standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have achieved UNICEF BFI Level 3 status and support our staff to develop their skills in supporting mothers to breast feed across Greenwich. Our service was described as ‘outstanding’ by NHS London / DH Peer review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas is committed to safeguarding and promoting the welfare of children and vulnerable adults and expects all staff and volunteers to share this commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is committed to equal opportunities promoting diversity, developing supporting policies and operates a variety of flexible working arrangements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that we require a minimum of six months post qualification experience to join our Bank.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joining as one of our bank workers is a great way to experience this for yourselves and meeting the passionate people who work for the Trust going the extra mile every day for our patients. Sound exciting? What are you waiting for - apply now.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For internal Staff looking to join the Bank in another role, please find further details under &#39;Joining the Staff Bank&#39; on the Trust&#39;s intranet site - The Ox.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julie Price, Operational Lead Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: julieprice@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:&lt;span&gt;07554 416 608&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
